result.name: Origami Kids Cafe

reviews.text: Great kids cafe but more suitable to toddlers that are comfortable in walking as it gets crowded on the weekend with children running wild, and quite noisy. Food is better than other kids cafe by comparison, but quite an inconvenient location if you're not driving. My son loves it though. Pricey but seems clean.
The cafe was fun because of the play area for kids. The food is tasty but the staff is very demanding. Recommend for families of 3+.
Great place for kids. Cafe is strategically located so you can enjoy a great view of the city of Hong kong. You cal also bring your own picnic and have a bite at the park outside of the cafe.
Really ideal place for a relaxed dinner while your kid plays around

A very kid-friendly place with a great variety of toys in different zones, i.e. kitchen & cookery, racing cars, baby feeding, slides, wooden beads pit, etc. This place is newly renovated with homey ambiance, thanks to the wooden cum off-white color of decor. Food served here is Chinese food, which is different from the typical western food like pasta, burgers & fries. Coffee here taste unexpectedly good & you would probably end up having 2 cups. The only limitation here is the relatively short time session of 2 hours.

地點偏遠這可以說是缺點亦可以是優點，因為交通不便人流較小，起餐廳玩完後小朋友仲可以出外跑跑跳跳等，餐廳地方感覺較細但都多野玩同乾淨，可能是第一轉，收費小朋友入場費$198有點貴  大人最低消費$100 玩兩小時，如果多小朋友又不是太抵玩，食物方面真係唔錯喎，叫了幾樣食物其實所有都好食，味道不太濃，時間又剛好至於兒童餐方面，如果大人食覺得有點淡，但相對小朋友來說是健康的，食物唯一的是份量較小最終都要出外食多餐，不過女兒過了一個愉快的早上。
兒童樂園，有多种主題，是益智玩樂天地。

reviews.text:
Very rude lady (she was some
Leader) at the taxi stand! She talks rude to people and even blocked a guest drop off because it was Uber.

The driver had a drop off with another guest and when driver wanted to drop them off she Radio some one and did not let him do it to prevent my pick up at the same area.

Taxis are not taking any credit cards here same as in terminal.
Great Terminal because of teh rooftop park. The terminal is huge, has coffee shop and some other shops with cosmetics and leather goods etc.
This is the cruise terminal ,we took the world dream cruise from here.

Very unorganized   they didn't learn from the others and was very badly design of the luggage pick up area.  
Nearly a thousand of passengers all crowded at the pick up area and were stacked at the exit.
There was no immigration or custom to clear. The congestion was no signs to diverse passengers to the proper transport. 
All passengers had to  stop at the exit to check which way to the shuttle or taxi which make everyone stop 30 seconds to check the signs.
I would never want to use that cruise terminal again.
Excellent.
